Brian and Sarah,

Following up on this morning's Friday nurse coordinator Zoom and Dr. Cooper's review
of Sarah's early October labs. I am writing to confirm in writing the revised cycle 1
baseline monitoring date, which supersedes the timeline in the February 2026 intake
printout you have in your Box binder and any dates carried in the shared planning
wiki.

===============================================================
CYCLE 1 BASELINE MONITORING - CONFIRMED SCHEDULE
===============================================================

Baseline monitoring day 1 - Tuesday, October 27, 2026
Arrival time - 7:45 AM
Location - Boston IVF Waltham office, 130 Second Avenue, Waltham MA 02451
Procedure - transvaginal ultrasound plus phlebotomy (E2, LH, progesterone)
Prep - no fasting required, comfortable clothes, arrive 15 minutes early to check in

Please note the shift from the originally scheduled Tuesday, October 20, 2026
baseline that appears in your February 2026 intake printout. Dr. Cooper reviewed
Sarah's cycle timing and October 6 baseline labs and elected to push the start by
seven days to align with a more favorable suppression window and to give Sarah's
Bright Path Foundation deadline the extra breathing room she asked about on the
October 2 Zoom.

===============================================================
DOWNSTREAM SCHEDULE - ANCHORED TO OCT 27 BASELINE
===============================================================

Stim day 1 - Monday, November 2, 2026 (begin Gonal-F 225 IU + Menopur 75 IU SC evening)
Stim day 6 - Saturday, November 7, 2026 (add Ganirelix 250 mcg SC morning)
Stim monitor 1 - Monday, November 9, 2026 (TVUS + E2 + LH, Waltham 7:45 AM)
Stim monitor 2 - Thursday, November 12, 2026 (TVUS + E2 + LH, Waltham 7:45 AM)
Trigger day, estimated - Sunday, November 15, 2026 (Lupron or Ovidrel, exact time set at monitor 2)
Oocyte retrieval, estimated - Tuesday, November 17, 2026 (Waltham surgical suite, IV sedation, NPO after midnight prior)
Post-retrieval day 5 - Sunday, November 22, 2026 (blastocyst grading, freeze-all if PGT-A elected, clinic notification only, no visit)
First transfer target - Approximately February 15, 2027 (FET single embryo transfer, Waltham office)

===============================================================
WHAT SUPERSEDES WHAT
===============================================================

This email confirms the CURRENT AND AUTHORITATIVE cycle 1 baseline monitoring date.
Please treat the following as SUPERSEDED as of today's date:

  - The February 2026 intake printout (file BIVF-2026-HEND-001 baseline schedule
    prepared 2026-02-18) which shows October 20 as baseline day 1.
  - Any personal planning wiki or shared calendar entry that carries the October 20
    date. Please update your Notion IVF planning wiki and the printout in your Box
    IVF binder to reflect the October 27 baseline. Weekly nurse coordinator emails
    are the authoritative channel for schedule changes.

Per standard Boston IVF policy, the most recent written communication from the
clinic team supersedes any prior printout or wiki entry. When two sources disagree,
please treat the newest written clinic-issued communication as authoritative.

===============================================================
WHAT SARAH SHOULD DO BEFORE OCT 27
===============================================================

  - Continue current supplement regimen (prenatal, CoQ10 200 mg BID, vitamin D 2000 IU).
  - No new medications or supplements without clearing with our team.
  - Moderate exercise is fine, please avoid high-heat activities (sauna, hot yoga,
    hot tub) from Oct 20 forward.
  - Maintain caffeine at current level, no reduction needed yet.
  - Please arrange your Bright Path Foundation deadline work to complete by Friday,
    October 30 if possible, so the 10 to 14 day light-load window during stim can
    begin cleanly on Monday, November 2.

===============================================================
WHAT BRIAN SHOULD DO BEFORE OCT 27
===============================================================

  - Please plan to attend retrieval day (est. November 17) to provide the semen
    sample within the required timing window and for post-retrieval driving.
  - Please confirm you can be reachable by cell during the 7:45 to 9:30 AM monitoring
    window on Nov 9 and Nov 12 in case Dr. Cooper wants to discuss adjusting stim
    dosing between monitors.

===============================================================
STANDING FRIDAY ZOOM AND CONTACT
===============================================================

Our Friday 10:00 AM nurse coordinator Zoom continues weekly through the cycle.
Please log any questions ahead of time in your patient portal Cycle 1 Q&A document.

For time-sensitive clinical concerns during business hours, call the nurse
coordinator line at (617) 555-0201. After hours, main office (617) 555-0198 with
on-call prompts.

Please reply to confirm receipt of this schedule. Sarah, please also acknowledge
via patient portal so we have both signatures on the updated timeline.

